    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-15T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/6–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d837fn1">Sent as 253, July 21, 5 p. m., to Seoul.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-15T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 15, 1948—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1296. Reference <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1209, July 2, 2 p.
                        m.<note n="2" xml:id="d837fn2">Not printed.</note> Foreign Minister<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d837fn3">Dr. Wang Shih-chieh.</note> has now informed us that
                    China will definitely join the US in any action to recognize a national
                    government of Korea. He suggests that the US and China undertake a joint <hi
                        rend="italic">démarche</hi> to secure simultaneous and similar British
                    action. He further suggests that the American Ambassador in Paris be instructed
                    to renew his efforts vis-à-vis French Government.<note n="4" xml:id="d837fn4">In
                        telegram 1045, July 17, 5 p. m., to Nanking, the Department expressed
                        appreciation of Chinese support, agreed as to appropriateness of parallel
                        statements by the U.S., United Kingdom, and China, stated it was “most
                        anxious that such joint action be arranged”, and was delaying further
                        approach to France pending a reaction to the circular telegram of July 10, 1
                        a. m., <ref target="#pg_1235">p. 1235</ref>. This telegram was repeated as
                        2800 to London and as 242 to Seoul.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
